    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-11T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-11T02:00:00-05:00" n="416"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9296: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-11T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 11 [<hi rend="italic">12?</hi>] 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 12—5 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>454. Secretary of the Joint Commission informs me that Japanese Consul General
                    has asked for an immediate meeting of the Commission as Chinese troops are
                    moving into the Shanghai area in violation of the 1932 Truce Agreement.<note
                        n="79a" xml:id="d416fn79a">Signed at Shanghai, May 5, 1932, <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_217">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 217</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
